    %p 25c Inc. is creating the Internet's "value graph".


    %p It empowers people to directly support what they value. And it makes it very easy for creators to receive support from lots of people in small amounts. Think fifty-thousand quarters.


    %p The 25c Button&trade; is a patented "multi-one-click" button that works just like a 'Like' button but includes a one-quarter-a-click micro-donation. Try it here to donate to 25c Inc.: [button]


    %p A page view is a page view for an advertiser. But for people certain page views have a lot more value than others. Like that one comment that saved you hours of hassle. Or that truly inspiring video.


    %p 25c Inc. is a privately funded company based in San Francisco, California. Founded in 2011 by Sylvio Drouin, Lionel Jingles, Francis Li, Ruza Markov and Martin Roscheisen, the company has developed a patent portfolio around easy-to-use sub-$1 social payments.

